India Builder Plans $500 Million Coastal Resort in Mauritius, Matinal Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-28T06:45:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/india-builder-plans-500-million-coastal-resort-in-mauritius-matinal-says.html
Patel Engineering Ltd. (PEC) , an Indian
construction group, plans to build a $500 million resort in Port
Louis, the Mauritian capital,  Le Matinal reported , without
saying where it got the information.  The 58-acre (23-hectare) coastal project, known as Neotown,
will consist of villas, a hotel, office parks and marine
gardens, the Port Louis-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  